                    "question":  "“Cannot be opened” / “unidentified developer” / “Apple cannot check” / “cannot verify” errors.",
                    "answer":  "macOS blocks unsigned apps by default — even safe ones. For a \u003ccode\u003e.dmg\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode\u003e.pkg\u003c/code\u003e: \u003cstrong\u003eControl-click\u003c/strong\u003e the file → \u003cstrong\u003eOpen\u003c/strong\u003e → \u003cstrong\u003eOpen Anyway\u003c/strong\u003e in the warning dialog. For other app types, try the same flow or go to \u003cstrong\u003eSystem Settings → Privacy \u0026 Security\u003c/strong\u003e and click \u003cstrong\u003eAllow Anyway\u003c/strong\u003e. Still stuck? Try \u003ca href=\"https://itsalin.com/appInfo/?id=sentinel\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eSentinel\u003c/a\u003e to sign or unblock the app."
